profile_positions.description:
•	Support the co-development of a sustainable platform to understand the primary care, public health and social care needs for dementia, with a focus on underserved populations (ComPHAD);
•	Carrying out a scoping review using a critical realism framework to explore complexities around dementia diagnosis in populations based on rurality and/ or housing instability;
•	Attending and writing up focus group and co-development activity reports with community organisations and other stakeholders, and inserting the findings to a critical realism framework;
•	Presenting findings of Messiha et al.'s (2022) systematic review work to the ECR/ MMCR networks who are carrying out co-development exercises within their own projects to help facilitate shared learning.

•	Work with the D+I team to optimize the existing strategy for increasing participation of conference attendees from low- and middle- income countries;
•	Contribute ideas that are relevant to the goals of the strategy;
•	Input on any administrative tasks;
•	Attend routine meetings; 
•	Give feedback on aspects relevant to the delivery of the strategy.

For more information about the strategy, refer to this link: https://isbnpa.org/isbnpa-strategic-plan-2022-2025/

•	Delivering scientifically rigorous evidence-based co-creation methodology for public health;
•	Researching about underpinning theories used for co-creation research in various fields including public health; 
•	Engaging in meetings and trainings to maximise exposure to developing skills and knowledge-sharing;
•	Giving scientific presentations and lecture about my work to advance the evidence-base about co-creation and enable collaboration;
•	Attending conferences to promote project work;
•	Participating with outreach activities using project work;
•	Leading on ‘Dissemination’ at project-level for 2022/ 2023.

•	Getting exposure into NGO’s youth participatory research and practice;
•	Attending and contributing to meetings;
•	Presenting my work to the employees of the Alexander Foundation;
•	Facilitating brain-storm activities based on my scientific research;
•	Leading research about the work of Stichting Alexander using Critical Social Theory of Empowerment, to culminate into a scientific article.

•	Teaching diverse materials related to research proposal writing and research methods;
•	Facilitating sub-group activities;
•	Assessing presentations and proposal writing;
•	Quality checking assessments on presentations and proposal writing.

•	Chairing feedback sessions in capacity of classes;
•	Preparing lecture content;
•	Guest lecturing two sets of a 90-minute class on policy/ programme (intervention) implementation in public health;
•	Creating and facilitating interactive class activities;
•	Assisting in teaching for another two sets of 90-minute class on implementation science theories, such as Theory of Change, in public health.

- Providing support on ARW’s Disease Specific Programmes™, through:
•	Creating DSP materials/ questionnaires;
•	Checking translations;
•	Gaining exposure to briefing agencies;
•	Undertaking data processing, analysis, and presentation;
•	Attending internal meetings/ client teleconferences;
•	Monitoring suppliers (fieldwork/ DP databases);
•	Liaising and monitoring the progress of fieldwork.
